0 Param data.1 string m_text: We had arranged to meet. I was so looking forward to it...
But before we had the chance...that man killed me. Just my luck.
I don't suppose you'd take me to the place we planned to meet, at least?
It was in Raom Meadows. Out front of the little house there.
Then I'll cross, I swear.
I know seeing him would only add to my anguish...
So in the end, I wanted to see the view we were meant to enjoy. Thank you so much.
I went for the tithing to go all-in on my next life. Never thought I'd end up Lost.
Guess I must have unfinished business. That's got to be it.
Actually, there's this girl who always sits in a chair west of the Dais of Life...
Don't suppose you could take me to see her?
I figure if there's something I'm holding on to, it must be her.
We grew up together, you see. Maybe I was worried she'd be sad.
It's not like I've got anything to say. I just want a look. Then I can be sure.
Thanks for tagging along. I'm ready now.
Kagachi... So we meet again. I bet you're thinking how awkward this is, right?
Even so... It's good to see you.
I want to tell you something. But we can't speak here... I'd rather someplace quiet.
I know. The Sook Fens would be perfect. Sorry to be a nuisance right to the end.
So, Kagachi.
Do you know what that voice is? In death, it's finally clear to me.
My dark thoughts, the stains and shame of my life, are now one with the voice.
It's a shadow...cast by souls spun together through reincarnation. And it's about to spill forth.
I wanted to let you know.
Sorry for...everything. I'm glad I got to see you one last time. Thank you.
My friends got me to join the uprising... But what was the point if it ended in death?
I have no idea why I went along with them. I should've gone to Kiho Shores instead.
I'd like to see it one more time... Would you take me there?
Around the entrance to the ruins would be best.
I love this place.
I get sad at times, even knowing how things work. Like when my friend died...
Whenever I felt down, I'd come here. It's a very special place to me.
I'm ready to leave now. Thank you.
How did I end up Lost? The Navigator's teachings are never wrong!
Never... Never wrong... Never?
Ever... Ev-Ever wrong?
Ev-Ev-Ever... Oh.
Hyah!
Hah... So it's you. Come to laugh at my misfortune?
Do what you will. It's not like I have the power to stop you.
All I can do, is linger on...
Please...
Will you heed my request, as a Watcher?
Take me to my mother's side. Lost though I am, I must be there for her.
Things may have been different, if Mother and I had led normal lives.
Seeing what she has become, that thought echoes in the corners of my mind.
But I have no regrets. I dedicated my life to her, and I'm glad for it.
The short time I've spent with you has showed me that.
I will stay with Mother a while longer.
Kagachi... I thank you.
Well, if it isn't that Executioner who snuffed me out.
When you killed me, I couldn't help but marvel at the display of strength.
So I don't really hold it against you, funnily enough. I've got unfinished business, though.
There's a twinblade sealed within ancient ruins. I want to track it down.
If you find it, show me, huh?
Yeah, that's the weapon all right.
Used to belong to a fellow thief and good friend. Ironic it was stolen.
I wanted to see it before I left. Now I'm good to go.
Hope I get to be a tough guy like you in the next life.
You're the Executioner!
Didn't expect you to come to me. I've been looking everywhere, trying to get my revenge!
Grraaar!
You... You're the guy who killed me, huh?
It doesn't really matter to me. I was destined to die that day. That's all.
If you die, you just get reincarnated. That's what I thought, so I don't get why I'm still here.
I don't know why I linger...but maybe going home will help sort it out.
My house is in the Mesid Woods. Can you take me there?
I had no idea my wife was so distraught at my death...
My faith in the precepts of reincarnation might have caused me to give up on life too easily.
It never occurred to me that it could make people so unhappy.
Perhaps I'm Lost because I led such an empty existence.
In the next life, I'll be sure not to let anyone down like this. Thank you... I'm ready now.
Isn't the Blood Guard amazing? I always looked up to them.
There's this guy, Zaav. He's a real man's man, cool as they come.
I was training to join the Blood Guard myself, but got killed by some Fallen...
I'd love to see a Blood Guard spear before I go. One upgraded to an Attack of 100 or more.
Ah, this is it, huh? I've wanted to hold one of these for ages...
Seeing it up close, it's just as glorious as I expected. Look at that gleaming point.
Well, that's the perfect thing to see me into the next life.
But I guess I won't remember anything when I cross over, huh? Heh.
That you, Kagachi? Look at me. Lost. Can you give me a hand?
I ran into a Daemon, ages ago. I couldn't handle Daemons back then.
So I asked them to join forces with me once I knew what I was doing.
I ended up dying...but they gave me something to aim for, so I want to talk before I cross.
They were on the ground floor of Ehir Palace. Could be gone by now, though.
They're not here...so I guess someone else got here first.
I'm just happy I got to come.
Try not to go dying on us, Kagachi. The Watchers are a ray of hope.
Have you heard of Jex?
Apparently one touch of it unlocks infinite wisdom. A girl called Lucika told me ages ago.
I doubt it's true, to be honest, but I want to see for myself.
I'll throw in the towel if nothing turns up, but will you help me out?
By the way, I hear it's found in a forgotten place. It apparently looks like a gigantic machine.
That's it! It fits the description exactly!
It just looks like a big chunk of metal to me...but they say it holds great power.
You might be the type who can harness that power.
I'll be going now. Thank you for lending a hand.
Are you a Watcher, by any chance? A living man Beyond the Veil, so you must be, right?
I was part of an experimental unit of Watchers, but my body failed to adapt to the Beyond, and I perished.
I want nothing more than to see my home before I leave. Could you take me to Kiraq?
This is where I come from. Nothing much here, I know.
I think we all have a special connection to the place we were raised.
I'm ready to go now. Thank you.
One day you're alive, the next, you're dead.
I was showing off to a girl I liked...but the Fallen killed me like it was nothing.
I wish I'd trained harder instead of slacking off.
It'd be nice to see her one more time. She should be near the well to the northeast of Deto.
Take me there, will you! I'm begging you!
Thank you. I don't have the guts to speak to her, so just a glimpse is fine.
In the next life, I'll make sure I have what it takes to protect the ones I love.
My daughter-in-law tricked me into tithing. I can't believe it. I must get back at her somehow.
Hngh!
I-I can't...
YAAARGH!
I hope she's okay...
Oh. Uh, I'm talking about a friend of mine who's scared of men.
I can't bear to leave her to fend for herself. Would you take me to her before I go?
She lives in a house near the stairs to the north of the Dais of Life.
I wanted to reassure her before I go... But I can see she'll be fine.
I hope one day she finds someone that helps her overcome her fears.
It'll only distress her if I spoke up, so I'll be going now.
I was killed by one of the Fallen... I want to see my mother before I leave. Can you help me?
Wait, I shouldn't...
I think my mother would do something drastic if she saw me, and break the laws of the land.
Sorry, let me rethink that. Can you take me somewhere close?
You should find my mother at the northernmost crossroads in Deto.
Thank you. I saw her, and that's enough for me.
I'd like to speak with my mother, but it would only crush her...
I've decided it's best I leave now.
Woof woof! Woof woof!
(Maybe he wants me to take him to his master?)
(They might be somewhere in Deto. Maybe I'll ask around at the stalls.)
Woof woof!
(I think he's saying thanks. Heh... That's the first time a dog's taken a shine to me.)
I'm an olfactory aficionado. Give me any scent, and I'll tell you what it is.
Although I guess this is hardly the time for that.
My last wish is for you take me to Tashir Canal. Just the entryway is fine.
I want its fragrant aroma to be the last thing I smell!
*sniff* Ahhh!
Yep, that's the smell. It's the best. Nothing even comes close!
I hope I get a whiff of this bouquet in the next life, too.
Help me. There are Fallen everywhere I go.
When I died, I became Lost, and found myself in an unfamiliar place.
Take me to Deto. The entrance will do. I beg of you.
Whew, almost didn't make it.
Huh? I'm already dead? A minor detail.
It's no picnic being hunted by the Fallen as a Lost Soul, either.
Anyway, I got to see the city I love, so I'm happy. Guess I'll cross now.
You're a Watcher! I bet ya know my buddies, then, huh?
Don't know who I mean?
Ioga and Wucan, of course! The famed Watcher duo!
You know that Goliath axe they wield?
I want to hold it in my last moments. Bring me one, will ya!
That's the one! Boy, look at that edge on it!
I owe the two of them a lot. They always made time for me, no matter how busy they got.
I used to think all Watchers were scary, but they proved me wrong.
I look up to them both. It's nice to have this reminder of them again before I move on.
Thanks!
Do you know Lord Leo?
Of course you do, right? He's so handsome and intelligent. Perfect in every way!
I'm his biggest fan, you know. I can't leave without laying eyes upon him one last time.
You ought to take me to him, quick. Otherwise, I'll have to make a scene.
Ah! He's so charming...
Oh! Look at that dignity and grace!
My eyes are all aquiver! *pant* *pant*
*cough*
If only I could gaze upon him forever... But it would go against the laws.
And that's tantamount to defying Lord Leo himself. I've seen what I came for. I'll cross now.
I am more devoted to Lady Sara than any other. Even in death, my fervor knows no bounds.
Do I want to be taken to Sara, you ask?
That's Lady Sara to you. And I wouldn't dream of doing anything so outrageous.
I heard of a place filled with the linnaea flowers Lady Sara is fond of, and want to see it.
So this is the place Lady Sara is so fond of. It truly is a lovely spot.
I pray that I can be of service to Lady Sara in my next life.
Regrets, huh? I've been an alchemist all my life, so I can't think of a thing.
Perhaps one regret is that I haven't proven the weapons I craft are the strongest.
How would you prove that, anyway?
Let me think. Show me a weapon with an Attack of 200 or more.
Then I'll know mine weren't the strongest, so I can move on.
So you actually found one, huh? It seems I've been outdone.
Well, I'll forge even stronger weapons in the next life! I'd better get started!
Apparently, people once traveled farther afield, and discovered seas at the edge of the world.
Some chose to live beyond the seas, too. Something called snow would fall from the skies there.
But now these lands are sealed away, with all contact cut off.
I'm researching the lands beyond the sea. Before I move on, I want to see a weapon crafted there.
I know it's a difficult request, but will you try?
So this is it?
It certainly has the unique construction you'd expect in such a place.
Though it seems there was once trade between us, few such items exist today.
Thank you for helping fulfill this impossible request. I'm ready to cross over now.
I was a historian.
My field of expertise was the Age of Magic, so I frequented many ruins until I was slain by the Fallen.
Examining the item I sought in my final days would help me unravel an age-old mystery, but that's a daunting proposal.
Hm? You want to know what the item is?
A weapon crafted in the Age of Magic.
Oh! That's it!
I see... So this goes here, and it works like this... Ha!
Now no stone is left unturned. Thanks to you, I won't be left to become Fallen.
Now I'm dead and Lost, I can continue my Fallen research safely. Sometimes death is the answer.
I can finally visit places I was told were too dangerous. So, take me to the Shadestone Quarry.
And I mean its innermost depths, understood?
I've always wanted to see this place. I identified Fallen here I've never seen before.
All the years of toil are now worth it.
As much as I'd like to ask for more favors, I've imposed enough already, so I'll cross over now.
Thank you.
I had the finest armor money could buy, but the Fallen stole it and killed me.
Now I've finally seen the light. It is weapons that are the key.
Before crossing, I want to see a really potent weapon. Something with an Attack of 150 or more. Help me find one.
This is it, huh? Yes, it has a real heft to it.
You can feel the power in it. Maybe if I had this, I'd still be alive.
But it doesn't help if I don't know how to use it. So I guess it wouldn't change a thing.
I'm glad I got the chance to see such a fine item in my final moments. Thank you.
You're a Watcher... I'm glad I ran into you. I want you to kill me.
I resorted to crime for the sake of my family, and was executed by the Watchers.
I see the error of my ways now. But I can't get my loved ones out of my head.
Seeing my wife and daughter again wouldn't rid me of these regrets... So I want you to end it!
Please! Help me! I... I think I'm going mad!
Any moment now, I could turn into one of those monsters!
Ugh!
Aaargh!
Whenever someone asked, I said I believed in the precepts of reincarnation, but I thought it was nonsense.
Being reborn when you die? Just not possible. That was how I always felt...
But the Beyond really existed all this time. And here I am, a Lost Soul.
Well, there is somewhere I'd like to go before moving on. A place called the Soul Cage.
I heard a rumor that there's no Beyond there. If the Beyond exists, maybe that rumor's true, too.
So there's really no Beyond here, huh? I wonder why.
Well, no sense racking my brain over it.
I had my fair share of gripes...but being with you helped me see it's not all that bad.
I have you to thank for that. Much appreciated.
Know what happens when you keep raging after you Manifest?
You turn into a living corpse. A living Fallen, to be precise.
And you can never return to the Living World. Just like me.
Kill this abomination I've become. I beg you.
